<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="400" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1225,2108,777,1366]" pageId="0" pageNumber="400">• Medium-sized, sexually dimorphic, largely arboreal marsupial, with short, stocky body and square, box-like skull; fused digits (syndactylous); large and flattened bare nose; and forward-facing eyes.</paragraph>
